If you think that the United States is now competative in the world, Take a look at the price of steel. Its cheaper at the moment to buy steel from Japan and ship it<br>
to Detroit, than it is to rail it there from the east coast. Why is that?<br>
Could it be that the Steel industry still refuses to convert to more efficient<br>
converters? Could it be the railroads like to price gouge? Beats me, Im a computer tech, not an economist. But I can tell you all the chips I see are made somewhere<br>
other than the USA. Yeah we are real competative, and all thanx to Reagan.<br>
